  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Add More Layers \r\n\r\nYou don't have to use just single tracks in <code style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 148, 202); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play sequential</code> blocks - you can also layer multiple tracks to play together after each other. Let's try that with this Espresso remix:\r\n\r\n**Try this:** \r\n- Add the `play together` chunks into the `play sequential` block. You can decide the order. Each chunk should play one after the other.\r\n\r\nPress <code style=\"background-color: #fca401; color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px1 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">Run</code> and listen to your song! You should hear four backing tracks underneath the lead vocals!",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
